  sodium: 1180 mg
time required: 35 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-chili-lime-glazed-beef-tenderloin-663bc958fe8a253ad9a7b2dd
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Sweet Potatoes{2} into ½-inch pieces. Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Halve, peel, and cut @Red Onion{1} into 1-inch-thick wedges.

Toss sweet potatoes, carrots, and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of oil, @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, divide between two sheets; roast on top and middle racks, swapping rack positions halfway through.)

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Quarter @Lime{1}.

Pat @Beef Tenderloin Filets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add beef; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} and cover with #foil{} to keep warm. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

> Swap in chicken or pork for beef; cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook pork to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in same pan over medium-low heat. Add scallion whites; cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant and tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @Hoisin Sauce{2%tablespoon}, @Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{1%ounce}, ¼ cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings), @Sweet Soy Glaze{2 1/2%TBSP} (5 TBSP for 4), and juice from half the lime. (Be sure to measure the sweet soy glaze—we sent more!)

Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce has slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Slice beef crosswise.

Divide beef and sweet potato–carrot jumble between plates in separate sections. Spoon sauce over beef.

Sprinkle @Sesame Seeds{1%tablespoon} over sweet potato–carrot jumble. Garnish everything with scallion greens and serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Slice chicken or pork against the grain.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.